3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with peer-to-peer networks, which are a type of social network. It also discusses the behavior of nodes in the network, which is related to information networks. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses mathematical analysis to study the routing time in Kademlia networks, which falls under the scope of information theory. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the performance of Kademlia networks in terms of routing time, which is related to network performance.
